BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Thanks Kristine! Here's the meeting invite. - jason\n__________
 ______________________\nFrom: Nelson\, Kristine L (kln8n) <knelson@virgini
 a.edu>\nSent: Thursday\, July 31\, 2025 1:27:14 PM\nTo: Bell\, Jason B (tk
 w9un) <tkw9un@virginia.edu>\nSubject: RE: Stellic Advising - Academics & C
 areer Intersection\n\n\nHello Jason.\n\nOur vacation was very relaxing and
  much cooler than Charlottesville was! I hope you have been able to have s
 ome time away prior to the start of the semester.\n\n\n\nI understand the 
 teams met last week (or on Monday)\, but I’d love to find time to meet w
 ith you. Next Monday or Wednesday is probably the best. Feel free to put s
 ome time on my calendar. Truth be told\, we are just getting the hang of S
 tellic and hope that it looks better next week for our rising 3rd year stu
 dents when they “officially” become Batten majors in SIS.\n\n\n\nI loo
 k forward to discussing processes further with you.\n\nBest wishes\,\n\n\n
 \nKristine Nelson\nAssociate Director of Academic Operations\n\nFrank Batt
 en School of Leadership and Public Policy\n434.924.9282\n\nSchedule an app
 ointment<https://login.stellic.virginia.edu/appointments/r/knelson>\n\nHou
 rs available: 9am-5pm Mon\, Wed & Thur.\n\nTue/Fri email BattenAcademics@v
 irginia.edu<mailto:BattenAcademics@virginia.edu> for timely assistance.\n\
 n\n\nFrom: Bell\, Jason B (tkw9un) <tkw9un@virginia.edu>\nSent: Wednesday\
 , July 30\, 2025 1:00 PM\nTo: Nelson\, Kristine L (kln8n) <knelson@virgini
 a.edu>\nSubject: Stellic Advising - Academics & Career Intersection\n\n\n\
 nHi Kristine\,\n\n\n\nI hope your vacation was enjoyable and relaxing\, an
 d less hot than Charlottesville these past weeks.\n\n\n\nAs I’ve continu
 ed on-boarding\, I finally completed Stellic training and am fully in the 
 system.  I wanted to circle back with you as a follow-up to the Academics-
 Career meeting in June and discuss where academic and career intersect wit
 h respect to advising.\n\n\n\nThings I’m thinking about:\n\n  *   Are th
 ere any pre-established business rules you’ve been operating with?\n  * 
   How are you doing referrals in Stellic?\n  *   Any other best practices 
 or suggestions?\n  *   Pathways\n     *   It looks like there are Batten U
 G pathways which layout the core courses and an internship\n     *   Is th
 ere opportunity to add career actions/suggestions to this?\n\n\n\nIf there
  is anything else that I should be aware of or lessons learned\, I certain
 ly appreciate your insights.\n\n\n\nThis is low on the list of priorities 
 as you get settled after vacation\, so if you have some time in the next c
 ouple of weeks to chat that would be great.\n\n\n\nWelcome back!\n\nJason\
 n\n\n\n\n\n--\n\nJason Bell\nAssociate Director of Career Advancement\n\nE
  tkw9un@virginia.edu<mailto:tkw9un@virginia.edu>\n\n\n\nUniversity of Virg
 inia\nFrank Batten School of Leadership and Public Policy\nGarrett Hall\n2
 35 McCormick Road\, L002C\nCharlottesville\, VA 22904\n\nbatten.virginia.e
 du<https://batten.virginia.edu/>\n\n[University of Virginia]<https://www.v
 irginia.edu/>\n
