BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Good afternoon\,\n\nGreat to see you yesterday! As a recap\, we
  talked about chunking decision-making into three discrete phases\, before
  spending some time familiarizing ourselves with Karsh\, Garrett\, and oth
 er outlying Batten spaces. Those drawings are attached for your review.\n\
 nThe phased approach we discussed includes the following components:\n\n\n
   1.  First\, identifying the location of student centers of gravity\, cen
 ters\, and labs\;\n  2.  Second\, identifying the location of staff teams 
 and identifying faculty spaces\;\n  3.  And finally\, identifying individu
 al assignments of offices.\n\nFor each step\, Sean Michael and I will pres
 ent a few different possibilities and highlight the tradeoffs for group di
 scussion. In October’s meeting\, we’ll talk through the first of those
  phases together.\n\nBest\,\n  James\n
UID:040000008200E00074C5B7101A82E0080000000000FA8CE97428DC01000000000000000
